obo:GO_0003674  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_384  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: SDS-digested freeze-fracture replica-labeling (SDS-FRL) was used to visualize Cav2.1 in the stratum oriens of the hippocampal CA3 area at high resolution. Cav2.1 was enriched in presynaptic active zones compared to extrasynaptic bouton surfaces. Active zones were identified by clusters of intramembrane particles (IMP) as well co-labeling for the presynaptic active zone protein Rim1/2.\n\nTwo Cav2.1 antibodies, one raised in a rabbit (Rb) and another one in a guinea pig (Gp) against different epitopes, labeled the same presynaptic active zone. These antibodies recognized intracellular epitopes on their target protein and thus were visualized by gold particles on the protoplasmic membrane half (P-face). Gold particles labeling the Cav2.1 subunit could not be found in Cav2.1-/- mice.\n\n14/4/2017 Pim\n- \"integral component of membrane ...\" part is derived from the TM domains of Cav2.1.. Experimental description: Adult and P16 Wistar rats, Cav2.1+/- and Cav2.1-/- mice were used." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099059 replaced by GO:0048787" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_384" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

